<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="730">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182062" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pepo Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pepo Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepo">Pheidole pepo</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="730">types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="730">
Etymology Gr 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182062" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pepo Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pepo Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepo">pepo</taxonomicName>
, melon, alluding to the unusual head shape of the major.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="730">
diagnosis A large, yellow member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
group, similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182072" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rotundiceps Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rotundiceps Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundiceps">rotundiceps</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182081" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole sphaerica Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole sphaerica Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphaerica">sphaerica</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182082" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subsphaerica Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subsphaerica Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsphaerica">subsphaerica</taxonomicName>
, easily distinguished by the following traits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="730">Major: head greatly swollen; clypeus and mandibles reduced proportionate to the head; outline of head in full-face view almost completely devoid of pilosity; in side view, profiles of both anterior dorsal half and anterior ventral half of head capsule densely pilose, but profiles of posterior dorsal and ventral halves bare of pilosity; propodeal spines long and acute. Minor: body slender; occiput narrowed, with nuchal collar; propodeal spines long and slender, i.e., needle-like. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.78, HL 1.66, SL 1.02, EL 0.22, PW 0.84. Paratype minor: HW 0.64, HL 0.80, SL 1.06, EL 0.16, PW 0.44.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="730">Color Major: head and appendages medium yellow; mesosoma, waist, and gaster yellowish brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="730">Minor: concolorous dark yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="730">range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="730">biology Collected in spiny bamboo (Guadua) forest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="730">Figure Upper: holotype, major. Lower: paratype, minor. COLOMBIA: Finca Los Guaduales, 10 km southwest of San Jose del Palmar, Rio Torito, Choco, 800 m (Charles Kugler). Scale bars = 1 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
